<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,153,827]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">
Fifth abdominal ventrite in females with quite large, well pronounced, weakly transverse pit. Vasculum of spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[262,345,657,684]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–8" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1866,1891]" captionTargetBox="[233,1296,195,1775]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[198,1388,166,1847]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 7–8. M. crassicollis (7), M. dicaprioi (8). 7a–b: habitus; 7c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.7 mm]; 7f: antenna [2.1 mm]; 7g: sclerites of endophallus [0.2 mm]. 8a–b: habitus; 8c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.7 mm]; 8f: antenna [2.1 mm]; 8g: sclerites I–II and dorsal spicule of endophallus [0.7 mm]; 8h: sclerites III–IV of endophallus [0.5 mm]; 8k: spermatheca [0.5 mm]. 7a–b: paralectotype; 8a–b: holotype. scI–IV: sclerites I–IV of endophallus; ds: dorsal spicule. Square brackets: length of scale segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3763884" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3763884/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Fig. 8k</figureCitation>
) slender, scarcely pigmented, with sinuose proximal branch, long distal branch and moderately pointed apex feebly bent downwards. Ampulla not pigmented, vaguely shifted on dorsal side of vasculum. Duct and sperm gland insertions perceptibly distinct. Duct uniform in size, slender, coiled, coils rather thick and quite regularly arranged. Distal portion of duct and insertion on bursa copulatrix damaged so as not detectable in the single available female.
</paragraph>
